Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,ageing: n.  老化\N\NLesson 37 The process of ageing\N\N37  衰老过程\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.52,0:00:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,First listen and then answer the following question.\N\N听录音,然后回答以下问题.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.51,0:00:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is one of the most unpleasant discoveries we make about ourselves as we get older?\N\N随着年龄增长,人类对自身最不愉快的发现是什么?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.91,0:00:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At the age of twelve years,the human body is at its most vigorous.\N\N人体在12岁时是生命力最旺盛的时期.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.56,0:00:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It has yet to reach its full size and strength,\N\N虽然在这个时期人的身材、体力还有待发展,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.76,0:00:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and its owner his or her full intelligence,\N\N智力还有待发展和完善,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.90,0:00:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihood: n.  可能性\N\Nbut at this age the likelihood of death is least.\N\N但在这个年龄死亡的可能性最小.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.24,0:00:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,infant: n.  婴儿\N\NEarlier,we were infants and young children,\N\N再早一些,我们是幼儿和小孩子,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.51,0:00:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and consequently more vulnerable;\N\N身体较脆弱;\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.63,0:00:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,later,we shall undergo a progressive loss of our vigour and resistance\N\N再迟一些,我们就要经历生命力和抵抗力逐步衰退的过程.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which,though imperceptible at first\N\N虽然这个过程起初难以觉察,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.50,0:00:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,will finally become so steep that we can live no longer,\N\N但最终会急转直下,简直再也无法活下去了,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.89,0:00:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,however well we look after ourselves,\N\N不管我们怎样精心照料我们自己,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.90,0:01:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and however well society,and our doctors,look after us.\N\N不管社会和医生怎样对我们进行精心照顾.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.95,0:01:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ageing: n.  老化\N\NThis decline in vigour with the passing of time is called ageing.\N\N生命力随时间的流失而衰退叫做衰老.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.36,0:01:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It is one of the most unpleasant discoveries which we all make\N\N人类发现的最不愉快的一个事实是:\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.77,0:01:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that we must decline in this way,that if we escape wars,accidents and diseases,\N\N人必然会衰老.即使我们能避开战争、意外的事故和各种疾病,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.73,0:01:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we shall eventually 'die of old age',\N\N我们最终也会"老死",\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.33,0:01:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and that this happens at a rate which differs little from person to person,\N\N衰老的速度在人与人之间相差甚微,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.13,0:01:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,odds: n.  可能性\N\Nso that there are heavy odds in favour of our dying between the ages of 65 and 80.\N\N我们最可能死亡的年龄在65至80岁之间.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.47,0:01:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of us will die sooner,a few will live longer on into a ninth or tenth decade.\N\N有些人会死得早一些,少数人寿命会长一些,活到八十几岁或九十几岁,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.95,0:01:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But the chances are against it,\N\N但这种可能性很小,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.88,0:01:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is a virtual limit on how long we can hope to remain alive,\N\N我们所希望的长寿实际上是有限度的,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.30,0:01:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,however lucky and robust we are.\N\N不管我们多么幸运,多么健壮.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.91,0:01:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Normal people tend to forget this process unless and until they are reminded of it.\N\N衰老的过程,不经提起,正常人容易忘记:一经提醒才会记起.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.91,0:02:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We are so familiar with the fact that man ages,\N\N我们对人总是要衰老的现象并不陌生,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.12,0:02:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that people have for years assumed that the process of losing vigour with time,\N\N多年来就已认识到:生命力随着时间流失而丧失活力,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.85,0:02:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of becoming more likely to die the older we get,was something self-evident\N\N人随着年龄的增长而接近死亡,这是不言而喻的,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.97,0:02:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,like the cooling of a hot kettle or the wearing out of a pair of shoes.\N\N就像一壶热水迟早会凉下来,一双鞋渐渐会磨破一样.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.83,0:02:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They have also assumed that all animals,\N\N人们不但认识到所有的动物,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.11,0:02:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,organism: n.  有机体\N\Nand probably other organisms such as trees,or even the universe itself,\N\N大概也认识到所有的有机物,如树木,甚至宇宙本身,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.48,0:02:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,must in the nature of things 'wear out'.\N\N从事物的本质上来说都会"磨损掉".\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.80,0:02:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Most animals we commonly observe do in fact age as we do,\N\N我们通常看到的动物都会像我们一样衰老,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.09,0:02:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if given the chance to live long enough;\N\N即使能让它们活得足够长久,也一样难逃衰老,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.48,0:02:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and mechanical systems like a wound watch,or the sun,\N\N像上紧发条的手表那样的机械装置,或太阳,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.01,0:02:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,thermodynamics: n.  热力学\N\Ndo in fact run out of energy in accordance with the second law of thermodynamics\N\N根据热力学第二定律,都会消耗完其能量,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.54,0:02:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,(whether the whole universe does so is a moot point at present).\N\N(整个宇宙是否如此,目前尚有争论).\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.99,0:02:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But these are not analogous to what happens when man ages.\N\N不过,这些衰老的情况同人并不相似.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.09,0:02:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A run down watch is still a watch and can be rewound.\N\N手表停了依然是只手表,还可以重上好发条.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.64,0:03:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,An old watch,by contrast,\N\N然而一只老掉牙的手表,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.30,0:03:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes so worn and unreliable that it eventually is not worth mending.\N\N磨损太厉害,老得一点儿也不准了,最终会不值得修理了.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.83,0:03:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But a watch could never repair itself,\N\N但是,手表决不会自行修理,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.22,0:03:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it does not consist of living parts,only of metal,which wears away by friction.\N\N它不是由有生命的部件组成,而是由金属组成,而金属可以因磨擦而磨损殆尽.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.61,0:03:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We could,at one time,repair ourselves well enough,at least,\N\N而我们人,在一定时间内是可以自行修复的,至少,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.59,0:03:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome all but the most instantly fatal illnesses and accidents.\N\N除了暴病而死或意外事故外,足以克服一切一般疾病和事故.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.66,0:03:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Between twelve and eighty years we gradually lose this power;\N\N在12岁至80岁之间,我们逐渐丧失这种能力,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.18,0:03:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,an illness which at 12 would knock us over,at 80 can knock us out,and into our grave.\N\N能使我们在12岁时病倒的疾病,到了80岁可能会使我们一蹶不振而进入坟墓.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.40,0:03:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we could stay as vigorous as we are at twelve,\N\N假如我们能保持12岁的旺盛生命力,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.00,0:03:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it would take about 700 years for half of us to die,\N\N那么我们当中的一半人过700年才会死去,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.07,0:03:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and another 700 for the survivors to be reduced by half again.\N\N剩下的一半人再过700年,才会又减少一半.\N\N